#Summary1=(human1) After finding out she is pregnant, a vlogger who is now seven weeks pregnant and due in mid-September tells about her feelings, her decision to document her pregnancy on her vlog, her diet and cravings, getting doctor's and midwife appointments and experiencing nausea and headaches.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) A woman shares her early pregnancy journey at 7 weeks, describing her initial anxiety and shock upon finding out, current symptoms like loss of appetite and headaches, and her decision to document the experience while expecting a baby in mid-September.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) A woman discovers her pregnancy, feeling anxious and overwhelmed about the life change. She tracks her symptoms and dietary shifts, choosing to document her journey through videos to process and share the experience. Initially daunted by others' pregnancy stories, she holds off telling others until she feels more settled.

#Summary4=(Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct) The author has just found out she is pregnant and is documenting her first trimester on YouTube, sharing her anxiety, struggles with appetite, and physical symptoms such as nausea and headaches, as well as her efforts to stay healthy and prepare for motherhood.

#Summary5=(Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct) A young woman shares her experience of finding out she's pregnant, initially feeling anxious and overwhelmed, but now ready to document her journey through the first trimester.
#Text=Hi everyone !
#Text=So I 'm just about to tuck into a crisp sandwich .
#Text=Salt vinegar squares are my crisp of choice .
#Text=And I 've got some apple juice because this signifies kind of my diet staples the last few weeks .
#Text=So I thought this was an opportune time to tell you all that a couple of weeks ago I found out that I am pregnant .
#Text=It 's the first week that I 've been actually able to say the words " I 'm pregnant " and have it not feel really weird .
#Text=I found out on , I think it was the 3rd of January .
#Text=Let 's just double check that .
#Text=No , excuse me , it was the fifth of January .
#Text=I found out on the fifth and that was because my period was late and I am never late .

#Text=As soon as I came off the pill my period came back pretty regularly and I started tracking my periods just because I knew the pregnancy was something that eventually we would want , and I know that it helps if you 've been tracking your period so you know your cycle .

#Text=And for the first few days / couple of weeks I felt really anxious , really scared , really worried , because my initial reaction was , and still now , I 'm a bit like , I 'm not old enough for this .
#Text=I 'm not grown up enough to do this .
#Text=You feel like you 're prepared , you 're in a , you know , in a relationship .
#Text=We have been for years , we 're adults , but I do n't know what it is .
#Text=As soon as I found out I just went back to like a 14 year old girl .
#Text=I 'm like " oh my god , what am I gon na tell my mom ? I ca n't be a mom . "
#Text=So really I was just very very overwhelmed and anxious so it took a few days for me to really process what happened .
#Text=It was quite a shock and it 's such a huge huge thing .
#Text=It 's life - changing , and so for the first couple of weeks that 's all I could focus on , was how life - changing it was and it was really scary .
#Text=I then started to talk to people about it , that made me feel better .
#Text=And , I 'm not really sure what I 'm trying to say .

#Text=I do n't want this to be too , like , all over the place but I decided I do want to document this some way , whether I – at first I was like , I do n't need to copy it on YouTube but I definitely wanted to document this in some kind of video form , just because it 's such a huge thing .
#Text=You ’re only pregnant for the first time once .

#Text=But I did want to document my first trimester to an extent , because when I first found out , I did start to watch videos of people 's first few weeks , but again , maybe because I was n't in a great headspace , that just frightened me , which again was because everyone was just saying how awful they felt , how excited they were , and I did n't feel excited .
#Text=I felt worried .
#Text=The thought of telling , like , my mom .
#Text=I cried when I told her because I felt so , just , like , oh my god .
#Text=I mean you , you feel quite bad when you feel like that , because it 's such a happy thing and now , you know , I – you know , I know I 've kind of accepted .
#Text=The shock has kind of sunk in .
#Text=And I am happy to tell people , but at first when you 're trying to get your head around it , it 's very daunting and you just feel awful thinking .
#Text=The thought of telling someone makes me want to burst into tears .
#Text=All these things going onto my head .

#Text=So that also then helped me to make the decision that I do want to document this , but I 'm probably going to do it , like , with hindsight , so I check in every now and again and just let you know how I 've been feeling .
#Text=But in terms of if I am sick or I 'm not feeling great , I 'm not gon na vlog whilst I feel like that .
#Text=I would n't want to vlog whilst I feel like that if I was just ill anyway .
#Text=And I just think it did n't help me seeing people at their worst at the very beginning , because all you hear is doom and gloom .
#Text=I decided to wait a few weeks before I even started to talk about it , so I think I 'm about seven weeks .
#Text=I am waiting for my first midwife appointment .
#Text=I went – I booked the doctors , because the NHS says you need to book a doctor 's appointment , but that was a waste of time and I felt quite bad about taking that appointment .
#Text=Because in my area you 'd have to self - refer , so I have n't had any kind of appointment or checkups or anything but I have been tracking – tracking –
#Text=I 've got an app called " what to expect " , put in my , you know , cycle situation and have an estimated due date , which is about mid-September .
#Text=In terms of symptoms , I mean I have n't felt the best , but I have been able to get through it .
#Text=I 've definitely struggled on some days but I have n't been sick .
#Text=The biggest thing for me is I have lost – I dipped , and I have lost my appetite .
#Text=There 's nothing I really feel like eating .
#Text=I do n't have particular aversions to things , I do n't feel really sick when I smell anything at the moment .
#Text=But there 's things that I do n't want to have , so like coffee , I just know that I do n't want that , and all I want is beige :
#Text=I want chips , I want white toast , it 's pretty much all I eat all day .
#Text=Pasta if I want something hot maybe , I 've had soup , but essentially starchy carbs and that 's quite normal it seems .
#Text=Like , everyone craves that at this point because you 're , you know , building a baby , so you need that energy .

#Text=So I do n't feel particularly great nutrition-wise , and I 'm trying to eat fruit where I can and veg when I can , but I 'm just sort of going with it , because I know there 's enough information out there that this is generally how it goes .
#Text=And then hopefully you start to feel a bit better .
#Text=I have felt nauseous and as everyone describes it , a bit jet - lagged , a bit cloudy in my head , and the worst thing for me has been headaches .
#Text=I have n't had them this week , but last week I had a couple of really really bad ones and I have n't had headaches that bad for years .
